1
00:00:02.544 --> 00:00:04.796  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Doctor]<i> In the beginning,</i>
<i>there is darkness,</i>

2
00:00:04.963 --> 00:00:07.633  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>the emptiness of a matrix</i>
<i>waiting for the light.</i>

3
00:00:07.799 --> 00:00:11.178  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Then, a single photon</i>
<i>flares into existence.</i>

4
00:00:11.345 --> 00:00:13.012  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Then another.</i>

5
00:00:13.180 --> 00:00:16.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Soon, thousands more.</i>
<i>Optronic pathways connect,</i>

6
00:00:16.517 --> 00:00:19.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>subroutines emerge</i>
<i>from the chaos,</i>

7
00:00:19.353 --> 00:00:23.065  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and a holographic consciousness</i>
<i>is born.</i>

8
00:00:25.150 --> 00:00:27.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I awaken into this world</i>
<i>fully programmed,</i>

9
00:00:27.694 --> 00:00:29.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>yet completely innocent,</i>

10
00:00:29.363 --> 00:00:31.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>unaware of the hardships</i>
<i>I'll endure,</i>

11
00:00:31.865 --> 00:00:35.452  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>or the great potential</i>
<i>I will one day fulfill.</i>

12
00:00:38.330 --> 00:00:41.416  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Computer, save revisions
and open Chapter One.

13
00:02:31.526 --> 00:02:34.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Captain's Log,</i>
<i>Stardate 54732.3.</i>

14
00:02:35.155 --> 00:02:37.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It's been three weeks since we received</i>
<i>Starfleet's instructions</i>

15
00:02:38.075 --> 00:02:39.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>in the last datastream,</i>

16
00:02:39.576 --> 00:02:41.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>and we're finally ready</i>
<i>to begin "Operation Watson."</i>

17
00:02:41.912 --> 00:02:43.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>We're all holding our breath.</i>

18
00:02:43.872 --> 00:02:46.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-The deflector's in position.
-Anything?

19
00:02:46.333 --> 00:02:48.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I'm picking up
a phased tachyon beam.

20
00:02:48.752 --> 00:02:50.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[Seven] There's a triaxilating signal
encoded in it.

21
00:02:50.754 --> 00:02:52.130  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
On screen.

22
00:02:52.297 --> 00:02:55.174  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>Voyager, this is Lieutenant Barclay</i>
<i>at Starfleet Command.</i>

23
00:02:55.342 --> 00:02:56.968  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>-Are you receiving this?</i>
-Can you clear it up?

24
00:02:57.135 --> 00:02:58.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I'm on it.

25
00:03:00.179 --> 00:03:03.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>Captain Janeway, it's a pleasure</i>
<i>to finally talk to you in person.</i>

26
00:03:03.809 --> 00:03:06.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
The pleasure's mine, Admiral.

27
00:03:06.269 --> 00:03:07.896  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
How's the weather
in San Francisco?

28
00:03:08.063 --> 00:03:09.898  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>Cold and rainy, as usual.</i>

29
00:03:10.065 --> 00:03:13.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
It sounds delightful.
Lieutenant Barclay,

30
00:03:13.443 --> 00:03:17.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
my congratulations on establishing
the first transgalactic com-link.

31
00:03:17.948 --> 00:03:19.783  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You've earned a place
in the history books.

32
00:03:19.950 --> 00:03:21.743  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>I can't take all</i>
<i>of the credit, Captain.</i>

33
00:03:21.910 --> 00:03:24.746  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>It was Harry and Seven who suggested</i>
<i>bouncing a tachyon beam</i>

34
00:03:24.913 --> 00:03:26.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>off of the quantum singularity.</i>

35
00:03:26.331 --> 00:03:28.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Just be sure to thank us
when you accept the Daystrom Prize.

36
00:03:28.834 --> 00:03:30.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>I wish we had more time</i>
<i>for small talk,</i>

37
00:03:31.128 --> 00:03:33.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>but the singularity</i>
<i>only stays in alignment</i>

38
00:03:33.422 --> 00:03:34.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>for 11 minutes a day.</i>

39
00:03:35.006 --> 00:03:38.009  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Eleven minutes are better
than none, Admiral.

40
00:03:38.176 --> 00:03:40.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
We appreciate all your work, Reg.

41
00:03:40.178 --> 00:03:41.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>We're going to leave it up to you</i>

42
00:03:41.888 --> 00:03:43.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>to determine how to allocate</i>
<i>the com time.</i>

43
00:03:43.932 --> 00:03:47.018  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>Admiral, um...</i>
<i>there was something else.</i>

44
00:03:47.185 --> 00:03:50.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>Oh, yes, uh, Mr. Barclay</i>
<i>has arranged a small gift</i>

45
00:03:50.856 --> 00:03:53.066  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>for you and your crew.</i>

46
00:03:54.526 --> 00:03:57.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>This is a live image</i>
<i>from McKinley Station.</i>

47
00:03:57.779 --> 00:04:01.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Uh, not too much cloud cover</i>
<i>over North America today.</i>

48
00:04:04.119 --> 00:04:05.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Quite a view.

49
00:04:05.996 --> 00:04:07.831  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you, Reg.

50
00:04:07.998 --> 00:04:14.755  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
In my hat, I hold 146 sequentially
numbered isolinear chips--

51
00:04:14.921 --> 00:04:17.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
one for every member
of the crew.

52
00:04:17.424 --> 00:04:19.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Each chip entitles the bearer

53
00:04:19.926 --> 00:04:22.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
to three minutes
of uninterrupted com time

54
00:04:22.721 --> 00:04:25.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
with his loved ones
back in the Alpha Quadrant.

55
00:04:26.641 --> 00:04:28.059  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good luck.

56
00:04:28.226 --> 00:04:29.853  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My mom's birthday
is next week.

57
00:04:30.020 --> 00:04:31.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This could be the best present
I ever gave her.

58
00:04:32.063 --> 00:04:33.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who's everyone else calling?

59
00:04:33.440 --> 00:04:34.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be calling my sister.

60
00:04:34.775 --> 00:04:36.902  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What about you, Captain?
-My mother, I hope.

61
00:04:37.068 --> 00:04:38.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Doesn't anyone want to know
who I'm calling?

62
00:04:38.779 --> 00:04:39.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Wait, wait.
Let me guess.

63
00:04:40.030 --> 00:04:43.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Um... Reg Barclay
or Dr. Zimmerman.

64
00:04:43.366 --> 00:04:45.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What makes you so certain
it's either of them?

65
00:04:45.285 --> 00:04:46.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, number six.

66
00:04:46.620 --> 00:04:47.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The lowest one yet.

67
00:04:47.954 --> 00:04:50.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You'll be talking to your family
the day after tomorrow.

68
00:04:50.415 --> 00:04:52.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
One hundred and thirty.

69
00:04:52.751 --> 00:04:54.795  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's about a month
and a half from now.

70
00:04:54.961 --> 00:04:56.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So much for Mom's birthday.

71
00:04:56.296 --> 00:04:58.924  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Apparently, the line forms here.

72
00:04:59.090 --> 00:05:02.302  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[Tuvok] Congratulations.
-Doc, how about a trade?

73
00:05:02.469 --> 00:05:04.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm willing to throw
in some Holodeck time.

74
00:05:04.971 --> 00:05:07.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Come on. It would mean
a lot to my mother.

75
00:05:07.808 --> 00:05:11.144  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I wish I could help, but I have
a very important call to make.

76
00:05:11.311 --> 00:05:13.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Here. Give your mom my best.

77
00:05:13.814 --> 00:05:14.981  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you sure?

78
00:05:15.148 --> 00:05:18.109  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've waited this long.
What's another six weeks?

79
00:05:20.779 --> 00:05:24.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I can hear the critics already</i>
<i>"A new voice has arrived."</i>

80
00:05:24.741 --> 00:05:29.246  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You could be the next K'Ratak,</i>
<i>or a modern-day Tolstoy.</i>

81
00:05:29.412 --> 00:05:32.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'd like to start distribution</i>
<i>by the end of the month.</i>

82
00:05:32.457 --> 00:05:36.044  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Uh, the material I sent
was only a working draft.

83
00:05:36.211 --> 00:05:37.754  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I need time to make revisions.

84
00:05:37.921 --> 00:05:40.632  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Well, if you insist,</i>
<i>but please do it quickly.</i>

85
00:05:40.799 --> 00:05:42.467  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will.

86
00:05:43.301 --> 00:05:44.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So tell me...

87
00:05:44.928 --> 00:05:46.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
what did you think
of the characters?

88
00:05:46.471 --> 00:05:49.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Oh, they're very real--</i>
<i>compelling.</i>

89
00:05:49.516 --> 00:05:51.434  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I almost forgot</i>
<i>they were holograms.</i>

90
00:05:51.601 --> 00:05:53.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who was your favorite?

91
00:05:53.436 --> 00:05:55.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Without a doubt,</i>
<i>that would have to be Lieutenant...</i>

92
00:05:55.939 --> 00:05:57.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What happened?

93
00:05:57.607 --> 00:05:59.776  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your time has expired.

94
00:05:59.943 --> 00:06:02.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You could've let the man
finish his sentence.

95
00:06:02.612 --> 00:06:05.949  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I believe your ego has received
enough stroking for one day.

96
00:06:07.659 --> 00:06:09.828  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[whistling upbeat melody]

97
00:06:09.995 --> 00:06:11.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, how's Reg?

98
00:06:11.997 --> 00:06:14.791  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll have you know I was speaking
with Ardon Broht

99
00:06:14.958 --> 00:06:17.168  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
of Broht &amp; Forrester.

100
00:06:17.335 --> 00:06:18.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The publishers
of the<i> Dixon Hill</i> series?

101
00:06:19.045 --> 00:06:22.716  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mm-hmm. Who are now
about to publish my work.

102
00:06:22.883 --> 00:06:24.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It seems you're not
the only one aboard

103
00:06:24.467 --> 00:06:26.469  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with a flair
for holographic narratives.

104
00:06:26.636 --> 00:06:28.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[chuckles]
Well, congratulations.

105
00:06:28.471 --> 00:06:29.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

106
00:06:29.639 --> 00:06:33.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, what's it about?

107
00:06:33.310 --> 00:06:36.688  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The adventures
of an intrepid doctor.

108
00:06:36.855 --> 00:06:38.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, sounds like fun.

109
00:06:38.648 --> 00:06:42.027  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, I've never thought
about trying to get my work published.

110
00:06:42.193 --> 00:06:44.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe I could talk to your people
about<i> Captain Proton.</i>

111
00:06:45.030 --> 00:06:47.949  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Broht &amp; Forrester deals in...
sophisticated literature.

112
00:06:48.116 --> 00:06:50.076  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What are you saying,
that I'm lowbrow?

113
00:06:50.994 --> 00:06:53.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not at all. I'd be delighted
to talk to them.

114
00:06:53.997 --> 00:06:55.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah. Thanks.

115
00:06:56.166 --> 00:06:59.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, when do I get to see this opus?

116
00:06:59.794 --> 00:07:01.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, it's not ready yet.

117
00:07:02.130 --> 00:07:04.633  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It was ready enough
for Broht &amp; Forrester.

118
00:07:05.550 --> 00:07:08.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe it could use
a fresh pair of eyes.

119
00:07:08.178 --> 00:07:10.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
After all,
you are a fellow author.

120
00:07:10.472 --> 00:07:12.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll cover the rest
of your shift.

121
00:07:15.185 --> 00:07:16.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, I almost forgot.

122
00:07:17.145 --> 00:07:18.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's it called?

123
00:07:18.813 --> 00:07:21.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Photons Be Free.</i>

124
00:07:22.859 --> 00:07:24.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Catchy.

125
00:07:25.862 --> 00:07:27.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Doctor]<i> I awaken into this world</i>

126
00:07:27.530 --> 00:07:30.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>fully programmed,</i>
<i>yet completely innocent,</i>

127
00:07:30.742 --> 00:07:33.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>unaware of the hardships</i>
<i>I'll endure,</i>

128
00:07:33.203 --> 00:07:37.499  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>or the great potential</i>
<i>I will one day fulfill.</i>

129
00:07:39.292 --> 00:07:41.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah... welcome.

130
00:07:41.628 --> 00:07:43.713  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've made an excellent choice.

131
00:07:43.880 --> 00:07:47.300  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're about to take part in a thrilling
first-person narrative.

132
00:07:47.467 --> 00:07:50.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You will take on the role
of an Emergency Medical Hologram,

133
00:07:50.887 --> 00:07:53.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the Chief Medical Officer
aboard the Starship<i> Vortex.</i>

134
00:07:53.807 --> 00:07:55.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Vortex?!</i>

135
00:07:55.350 --> 00:07:59.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As our story begins,
an anomaly has hurled your ship

136
00:07:59.354 --> 00:08:00.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
thousands of light-years
across the galaxy.

137
00:08:00.939 --> 00:08:01.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your mission?

138
00:08:02.148 --> 00:08:04.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
To uphold your medical
and ethical standards

139
00:08:04.234 --> 00:08:08.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
as you struggle against the crew's
bigotry and intolerance.

140
00:08:08.738 --> 00:08:10.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Persons with vascular disorders
should consult

141
00:08:10.573 --> 00:08:12.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
a physician before running this program.

142
00:08:12.325 --> 00:08:14.744  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And now, a few acknowledgments.

143
00:08:14.911 --> 00:08:16.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
First, Dr. Lewis Zimmerman,

144
00:08:16.663 --> 00:08:19.249  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the creator of my holo-matrix,
whose foresight

145
00:08:19.416 --> 00:08:21.042  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and dedication have made it
possible for me...

146
00:08:21.209 --> 00:08:24.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Computer, freeze program.
How much longer is this introduction?

147
00:08:24.671 --> 00:08:27.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[computer] Nine minutes, four seconds.
-[sighs]

148
00:08:27.424 --> 00:08:29.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Skip to the first chapter.

149
00:08:29.926 --> 00:08:32.012  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Doctor] Chapter One
<i>"A Healer is Born,"</i>

150
00:08:32.178 --> 00:08:35.306  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>in which our protagonist</i>
<i>must make a difficult choice.</i>

151
00:08:37.767 --> 00:08:39.853  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman] Increase the resonance level,
20 percent.

152
00:08:40.020 --> 00:08:41.021  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you the EMH?

153
00:08:41.187 --> 00:08:42.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Please state the nature
of the medical emergency.

154
00:08:42.939 --> 00:08:44.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Our doctor's dead.
We've got wounded.

155
00:08:44.899 --> 00:08:47.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They're both badly hurt.
Who should we treat first?

156
00:08:47.360 --> 00:08:48.403  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh...

157
00:08:50.447 --> 00:08:52.365  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Second degree plasma burns.

158
00:08:54.909 --> 00:08:56.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's got an aortic rupture.

159
00:08:56.244 --> 00:08:58.413  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get him to the Surgical Bay now.

160
00:09:00.582 --> 00:09:02.751  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You! Over here.

161
00:09:05.086 --> 00:09:06.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whew.

162
00:09:12.677 --> 00:09:14.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Nice mustache.
-What?

163
00:09:15.013 --> 00:09:16.973  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, nothing.

164
00:09:19.809 --> 00:09:21.311  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's got a mild concussion.

165
00:09:21.478 --> 00:09:24.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm going to have to treat
the others first.

166
00:09:24.189 --> 00:09:26.024  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I need Lieutenant Marseilles
on the Bridge.

167
00:09:26.191 --> 00:09:27.817  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You'll treat him now.
-As I understand it,

168
00:09:27.984 --> 00:09:30.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
my job is to treat
the critical patients first.

169
00:09:30.820 --> 00:09:32.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, if you'll excuse me...

170
00:09:34.074 --> 00:09:36.076  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know who you think
you are, Hologram,

171
00:09:36.242 --> 00:09:38.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but to me, you're just
another piece of technology.

172
00:09:38.495 --> 00:09:41.664  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, apparently, I'm a piece
of technology that's in demand,

173
00:09:41.831 --> 00:09:42.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so why don't you
go back to the Bridge

174
00:09:43.041 --> 00:09:45.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and let me do my job?

175
00:09:45.543 --> 00:09:47.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's going on here?

176
00:09:47.420 --> 00:09:49.923  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Our medical hologram
is refusing to treat Mr. Marseilles.

177
00:09:51.841 --> 00:09:54.844  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Are you malfunctioning?
-I don't think so.

178
00:09:55.011 --> 00:09:57.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I need my helmsman
back at his station.

179
00:09:57.180 --> 00:09:59.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Lieutenant Marseilles
isn't seriously hurt.

180
00:09:59.349 --> 00:10:02.018  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This man will be dead
in five minutes if I don't operate.

181
00:10:03.478 --> 00:10:04.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Drop the force field.

182
00:10:17.659 --> 00:10:18.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That patient is dead.

183
00:10:19.160 --> 00:10:21.454  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now you're free to treat
Lieutenant Marseilles.

184
00:10:28.920 --> 00:10:31.798  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then the Captain
pulls out a phaser

185
00:10:31.965 --> 00:10:34.217  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and shoots him,
right there on the bio-bed.

186
00:10:34.384 --> 00:10:36.302  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Captain Janeway
murders a crewman?

187
00:10:36.469 --> 00:10:37.929  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Paris] No, Captain Jenkins.

188
00:10:38.096 --> 00:10:39.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Everybody has a different name.

189
00:10:39.472 --> 00:10:44.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're Kymble, you're Torrey,
and I am Lieutenant Marseilles.

190
00:10:44.435 --> 00:10:45.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, now, that's creative.

191
00:10:46.104 --> 00:10:47.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What did you say to the Doctor?

192
00:10:47.480 --> 00:10:49.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, he thinks
he's written a masterpiece.

193
00:10:49.399 --> 00:10:50.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I didn't know what to tell him.

194
00:10:50.775 --> 00:10:52.694  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If this gets distributed,

195
00:10:52.861 --> 00:10:54.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
people are going to assume
this is about us.

196
00:10:54.946 --> 00:10:56.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What are our families
going to think?

197
00:10:56.489 --> 00:10:58.616  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is a Starfleet ship.
No one will believe

198
00:10:58.783 --> 00:11:01.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we actually go around
shooting injured crewmen.

199
00:11:01.578 --> 00:11:04.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
People may not take
the program literally,

200
00:11:04.747 --> 00:11:07.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but they might wonder
if there's some truth to it.

201
00:11:07.750 --> 00:11:10.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[sighs] I think we should
talk to the Captain.

202
00:11:11.546 --> 00:11:14.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you sure you're not taking this
a little personally?

203
00:11:14.257 --> 00:11:15.633  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you mean?

204
00:11:15.800 --> 00:11:18.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, the Holodeck
always has been your domain.

205
00:11:19.012 --> 00:11:22.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[disbelieving laugh]
You--you think I'm jealous?

206
00:11:22.599 --> 00:11:23.558  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckling]

207
00:11:23.725 --> 00:11:25.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay, maybe I am overreacting.

208
00:11:26.144 --> 00:11:27.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why don't the rest of you
try the program

209
00:11:27.812 --> 00:11:29.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and decide for yourselves?

210
00:11:33.026 --> 00:11:34.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Doctor]<i> Chapter Five</i>

211
00:11:34.360 --> 00:11:36.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>"Out of the Frying Pan,"</i>
<i>in which our protagonist</i>

212
00:11:36.738 --> 00:11:39.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>must confront abusive colleagues.</i>

213
00:11:39.199 --> 00:11:41.034  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm here for my physical.

214
00:11:41.201 --> 00:11:43.912  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why don't you have a seat
over here?

215
00:11:45.747 --> 00:11:49.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Doctor, you better
get down to Engineering.

216
00:11:49.334 --> 00:11:50.335  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's wrong?

217
00:11:50.501 --> 00:11:52.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A plasma conduit just exploded.

218
00:11:53.046 --> 00:11:54.797  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
At least ten people are hurt.

219
00:11:59.802 --> 00:12:01.346  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, genius.

220
00:12:01.512 --> 00:12:03.223  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Forgetting something?

221
00:12:03.389 --> 00:12:05.558  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your mobile emitter?

222
00:12:06.559 --> 00:12:07.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, right.

223
00:12:09.896 --> 00:12:11.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't see it.

224
00:12:14.692 --> 00:12:16.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's my mobile emitter?

225
00:12:22.408 --> 00:12:25.119  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[grunts]
This thing must weigh 50 kilos.

226
00:12:25.286 --> 00:12:27.163  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You should be glad we let you
out of your cage at all.

227
00:12:27.330 --> 00:12:29.540  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, get going.

228
00:12:29.707 --> 00:12:31.125  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighing]

229
00:12:36.631 --> 00:12:38.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm impressed.

230
00:12:38.258 --> 00:12:40.009  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Really?
-Absolutely.

231
00:12:40.176 --> 00:12:43.513  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I haven't seen a dilithium matrix
this far out of alignment

232
00:12:43.680 --> 00:12:46.474  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
since I served aboard
a Ferengi garbage scow.

233
00:12:46.641 --> 00:12:49.018  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll fix it myself.

234
00:12:49.185 --> 00:12:50.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Excuse me.

235
00:12:50.812 --> 00:12:52.814  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How many times have I told you?

236
00:12:52.981 --> 00:12:55.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Engineering is off-limits
to holograms.

237
00:12:56.067 --> 00:12:58.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe you should waive
that restriction during emergencies.

238
00:13:00.196 --> 00:13:02.949  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A plasma conduit exploded?

239
00:13:03.116 --> 00:13:06.244  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Does it look like anyone here
is covered with plasma burns?

240
00:13:06.411 --> 00:13:09.914  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Lieutenant Par... uh, Marseilles
told me there was an accident.

241
00:13:10.081 --> 00:13:12.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Looks like your auditory subroutines
are malfunctioning... again.

242
00:13:13.126 --> 00:13:16.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm surprised a matrix as primitive
as yours can function at all.

243
00:13:17.880 --> 00:13:19.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe you should be a little
nicer to your shipmates.

244
00:13:20.008 --> 00:13:22.010  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You never know
when you might need their help.

245
00:13:22.176 --> 00:13:24.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Get one thing straight.
You're not one of my shipmates.

246
00:13:24.512 --> 00:13:26.764  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're a tool--
like this hyperspanner--

247
00:13:26.931 --> 00:13:27.932  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and tools can be replaced.

248
00:13:28.099 --> 00:13:29.517  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, why don't you go back
to Sick Bay

249
00:13:29.684 --> 00:13:32.353  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
before I start doing
a little reprogramming?

250
00:13:37.650 --> 00:13:39.652  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[soft, passionate moaning]

251
00:13:39.818 --> 00:13:41.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Computer, lights.

252
00:13:41.571 --> 00:13:42.864  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[startled grunts]

253
00:13:44.449 --> 00:13:46.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Didn't I tell you
to go to Engineering?

254
00:13:46.617 --> 00:13:49.037  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, I get it.

255
00:13:49.203 --> 00:13:52.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Interesting plot twist.
You get me out of Sick Bay,

256
00:13:52.415 --> 00:13:54.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so you're free to give
my patient a tonsillectomy.

257
00:13:54.667 --> 00:13:57.462  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you even think about
mentioning this to my wife,

258
00:13:57.628 --> 00:14:00.798  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I will purge your memory buffer.
Do we understand each other?

259
00:14:02.508 --> 00:14:04.469  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm here for my physical?

260
00:14:07.722 --> 00:14:10.683  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Doctor]<i> Chapter Six</i>
<i>"Duel in the Ready Room,"</i>

261
00:14:10.849 --> 00:14:13.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>in which our protagonist</i>
<i>faces an inquisition.</i>

262
00:14:13.603 --> 00:14:16.314  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This time, you've gone too far.

263
00:14:16.481 --> 00:14:19.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Captain, I'm not sure
what you mean.

264
00:14:21.736 --> 00:14:24.989  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
An inventory
of your holo-matrix.

265
00:14:25.156 --> 00:14:29.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
50 gigaquads of memory
devoted to music,

266
00:14:29.369 --> 00:14:31.287  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
42 for "daydreams,"

267
00:14:31.454 --> 00:14:35.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
another ten
to expand your sexuality.

268
00:14:36.709 --> 00:14:39.170  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I had no idea
holograms could do that.

269
00:14:39.337 --> 00:14:42.131  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
These extracurricular subroutines
don't belong

270
00:14:42.298 --> 00:14:45.468  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
as part of
an Emergency Medical Hologram.

271
00:14:46.427 --> 00:14:48.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do you have anything
to say for yourself?

272
00:14:48.888 --> 00:14:52.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, well, uh, of course I do.

273
00:14:52.308 --> 00:14:55.561  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't think these subroutines
are trivial, Captain.

274
00:14:55.728 --> 00:14:58.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They help make me
a better doctor

275
00:14:58.189 --> 00:15:00.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-and a better person.
-But you're not a person.

276
00:15:00.900 --> 00:15:03.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You may be programmed
to look and act human,

277
00:15:03.319 --> 00:15:04.862  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but that doesn't make you one.

278
00:15:05.029 --> 00:15:07.907  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
These subroutines are going
to be deleted immediately.

279
00:15:08.074 --> 00:15:09.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tulak.

280
00:15:13.996 --> 00:15:17.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Take the EMH to the Holo-Lab
for reprogramming.

281
00:15:23.756 --> 00:15:25.216  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Doctor]<i> Chapter Seven</i>
<i>"The Escape,"</i>

282
00:15:25.383 --> 00:15:28.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>in which our protagonist</i>
<i>is aided by his only ally.</i>

283
00:15:28.344 --> 00:15:30.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not sure we should
be doing this, Commander.

284
00:15:31.013 --> 00:15:32.557  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Listen to him,
he knows what he's talking about.

285
00:15:32.723 --> 00:15:35.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Quiet!
I'm not talking to you.

286
00:15:35.351 --> 00:15:37.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If we start tinkering
with his matrix,

287
00:15:37.395 --> 00:15:39.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
how do we know we won't
accidentally delete

288
00:15:39.397 --> 00:15:40.857  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
some of his diagnostic subroutines?

289
00:15:41.023 --> 00:15:42.066  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckling]

290
00:15:42.233 --> 00:15:45.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You afraid you'll catch something
on your next away mission, Ensign?

291
00:15:45.361 --> 00:15:47.864  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There must be millions of viruses
in this Quadrant

292
00:15:48.030 --> 00:15:49.866  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that no one's ever encountered before.

293
00:15:50.032 --> 00:15:52.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
With my luck, I'll probably end up
catching half of them.

294
00:15:53.077 --> 00:15:55.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Great, my character's
a hypochondriac.

295
00:15:55.663 --> 00:15:57.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll escort the prisoner from here.

296
00:15:58.040 --> 00:16:00.710  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Our orders are to take him
to the Holo-Lab.

297
00:16:00.877 --> 00:16:03.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been ordered
to perform the procedure.

298
00:16:03.588 --> 00:16:08.217  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your sympathies for the EMH
are no secret, Three of Eight.

299
00:16:10.970 --> 00:16:13.639  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Step aside.

300
00:16:27.695 --> 00:16:29.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Run, Doctor!

301
00:16:32.950 --> 00:16:34.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

302
00:16:36.245 --> 00:16:38.623  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

303
00:16:38.789 --> 00:16:40.917  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Doctor]<i> Chapter Eight</i>
<i>"A Tragic End,"</i>

304
00:16:41.083 --> 00:16:43.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>in which our protagonist</i>
<i>learns his fate.</i>

305
00:16:43.711 --> 00:16:45.755  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Jenkins] I've tried to do this
the easy way,

306
00:16:45.922 --> 00:16:47.965  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but it's clear you're not going
to be reasonable.

307
00:16:48.132 --> 00:16:50.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your matrix will be decompiled
and reinitialized.

308
00:16:50.843 --> 00:16:53.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You'll remain off-line
except for emergencies.

309
00:16:53.971 --> 00:16:55.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ready.

310
00:16:55.431 --> 00:16:56.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do it.

311
00:16:56.933 --> 00:16:58.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Three] Wait.

312
00:17:00.102 --> 00:17:02.522  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He has the right
to expand his program.

313
00:17:02.688 --> 00:17:05.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's a piece of technology.

314
00:17:05.608 --> 00:17:06.776  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He has no rights.

315
00:17:06.943 --> 00:17:08.277  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But he should.

316
00:17:08.444 --> 00:17:10.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
One day, the EMH
and others like him

317
00:17:10.947 --> 00:17:13.115  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
will be recognized
for what they are--

318
00:17:13.282 --> 00:17:16.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
intelligent individuals
with a passion for life.

319
00:17:16.244 --> 00:17:18.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Make no mistake, Captain--

320
00:17:18.746 --> 00:17:21.332  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we may be thousands
of light-years from home,

321
00:17:21.499 --> 00:17:24.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but one day, people will learn of
the crime you're committing here today.

322
00:17:25.086 --> 00:17:28.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nice speech.

323
00:17:28.464 --> 00:17:30.216  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now decompile the program.

324
00:17:38.558 --> 00:17:41.686  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What you've experienced,
dear protagonist,

325
00:17:41.852 --> 00:17:43.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
is a work of fiction.

326
00:17:43.604 --> 00:17:47.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But like all fiction,
it has elements of truth.

327
00:17:47.441 --> 00:17:49.443  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I hope you now have
a better understanding

328
00:17:49.610 --> 00:17:52.446  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of the struggles
holograms must endure

329
00:17:52.613 --> 00:17:54.782  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in a world controlled...

330
00:17:54.949 --> 00:17:56.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
by organics.

331
00:17:57.910 --> 00:18:00.037  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[computer] End of program.

332
00:18:02.164 --> 00:18:03.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Janeway to the Doctor.

333
00:18:04.041 --> 00:18:06.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Report to my ready room now.

334
00:18:10.881 --> 00:18:13.009  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How many times
do you want me to say it?

335
00:18:13.175 --> 00:18:15.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My work is not
about the<i> Voyager</i> crew.

336
00:18:15.344 --> 00:18:18.014  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Come on. Ensign Kymble,
Lieutenant Marseilles...

337
00:18:18.180 --> 00:18:21.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The characters look
almost exactly like us.

338
00:18:21.267 --> 00:18:23.686  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I used your physical parameters
as a starting point,

339
00:18:23.853 --> 00:18:27.732  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I assure you any further similarities
are purely coincidental.

340
00:18:27.898 --> 00:18:31.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You set your story on a starship
lost in the Delta Quadrant.

341
00:18:31.360 --> 00:18:33.070  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What would you have me
write about?

342
00:18:33.237 --> 00:18:35.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Palace intrigue
on the Klingon Homeworld?

343
00:18:35.948 --> 00:18:38.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I do what all good novelists do.
I write what I know.

344
00:18:39.035 --> 00:18:41.037  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, it is about<i> Voyager?</i>

345
00:18:41.203 --> 00:18:42.246  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

346
00:18:42.413 --> 00:18:44.123  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The<i> Vortex</i> characters
are larger than life.

347
00:18:44.290 --> 00:18:47.460  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They're nothing like our crew.
As far as I know, Captain,

348
00:18:47.627 --> 00:18:50.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you haven't executed
any of my patients.

349
00:18:50.254 --> 00:18:54.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Doctor, you've written
a very imaginative story,

350
00:18:54.258 --> 00:18:57.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but it's conceivable that people
will think it's based on fact.

351
00:18:57.470 --> 00:18:59.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't see how.

352
00:18:59.305 --> 00:19:01.098  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How many holograms
carry mobile emitters?

353
00:19:01.265 --> 00:19:04.352  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The emitter in my story
is nothing like the real one.

354
00:19:04.518 --> 00:19:05.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, what was the point of that?

355
00:19:06.145 --> 00:19:08.314  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It was like carrying around
a small shuttlecraft.

356
00:19:08.481 --> 00:19:12.109  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's a metaphor, a symbol of the burdens
that I live with every day.

357
00:19:12.276 --> 00:19:15.237  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Imagine having to take this
everywhere you go.

358
00:19:15.404 --> 00:19:18.616  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It would be a constant reminder
that you're different from everyone else.

359
00:19:18.783 --> 00:19:22.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I wanted the player to feel
the weight of it... literally.

360
00:19:23.162 --> 00:19:26.624  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your emitter isn't a ball and chain.
It liberates you.

361
00:19:26.791 --> 00:19:30.002  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It doesn't always feel that way.

362
00:19:30.169 --> 00:19:32.004  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If I didn't know better,
I'd think this story

363
00:19:32.171 --> 00:19:34.340  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
was written by someone
who feels oppressed.

364
00:19:34.507 --> 00:19:36.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Is that how
you see yourself, Doctor?

365
00:19:36.842 --> 00:19:38.594  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Of course not.

366
00:19:38.761 --> 00:19:42.014  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The real victims are my brothers
in the Alpha Quadrant.

367
00:19:42.181 --> 00:19:43.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Brothers?

368
00:19:43.349 --> 00:19:45.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hundreds of EMH Mark-1's,

369
00:19:45.518 --> 00:19:48.646  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
identical to me
in every respect, except...

370
00:19:48.813 --> 00:19:51.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
they've been condemned
to a menial existence--

371
00:19:51.816 --> 00:19:53.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
scrubbing conduits,

372
00:19:53.901 --> 00:19:55.986  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
mining dilithium.

373
00:19:56.153 --> 00:19:57.905  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's a long history

374
00:19:58.072 --> 00:20:01.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of writers drawing attention
to the plight of the oppressed.

375
00:20:01.575 --> 00:20:04.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The Vedek's Song,</i> for example tells
the story of the occupation of Bajor.

376
00:20:04.620 --> 00:20:07.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I understand you have your reasons
for writing this,

377
00:20:07.498 --> 00:20:10.751  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but you should consider how it's going
to make your friends feel.

378
00:20:16.590 --> 00:20:19.260  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry my work offends you,

379
00:20:19.427 --> 00:20:21.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but if the price
of expressing myself

380
00:20:22.012 --> 00:20:24.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is having to suffer the scorn
of a few colleagues...

381
00:20:24.932 --> 00:20:25.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
so be it.

382
00:20:27.518 --> 00:20:30.146  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door opens, closes]

383
00:20:30.312 --> 00:20:32.732  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You're very popular</i>
<i>with my eighth graders.</i>

384
00:20:32.898 --> 00:20:36.819  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It's all they ever talk about.</i>
Voyager<i> this,</i> Voyager<i> that.</i>

385
00:20:36.986 --> 00:20:38.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Your mother has a small favor</i>
<i>to ask of you.</i>

386
00:20:38.988 --> 00:20:40.156  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kim] Name it.

387
00:20:40.322 --> 00:20:43.117  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I was hoping you could</i>
<i>record a short presentation</i>

388
00:20:43.284 --> 00:20:45.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>about what it's like</i>
<i>to command a starship.</i>

389
00:20:45.953 --> 00:20:48.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But... I don't command
a starship.

390
00:20:48.664 --> 00:20:51.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>In your letters, you said the Captain</i>
<i>puts you in charge sometimes.</i>

391
00:20:51.584 --> 00:20:53.419  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

392
00:20:53.586 --> 00:20:57.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What I said was I'm in command
of the night shift...

393
00:20:57.715 --> 00:20:59.008  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
twice a week.

394
00:20:59.175 --> 00:21:02.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>She must think very highly of you</i>
<i>to give you so much responsibility.</i>

395
00:21:03.053 --> 00:21:04.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>So, when is she</i>
<i>giving you a promotion?</i>

396
00:21:06.056 --> 00:21:07.475  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kim] Uh...

397
00:21:07.641 --> 00:21:10.519  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[clears throat]
It's a small ship.

398
00:21:10.686 --> 00:21:13.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There are only so many
command positions available.

399
00:21:13.814 --> 00:21:17.026  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>This Captain Janeway</i>
<i>sounds like a lovely woman.</i>

400
00:21:17.193 --> 00:21:19.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>-Maybe I should write her.</i>
-Mom!

401
00:21:19.487 --> 00:21:20.946  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>She needs to know how hard you work.</i>

402
00:21:21.113 --> 00:21:22.740  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Please, don't get involved.

403
00:21:22.907 --> 00:21:25.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>[staticky]</i>
<i>Harry, I can't hear you.</i>

404
00:21:25.785 --> 00:21:28.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Seven] A solar flare
is scattering the beam.

405
00:21:28.746 --> 00:21:31.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Mrs. Kim]<i> Tell Captain Janeway</i>
<i>to expect a letter from me.</i>

406
00:21:31.457 --> 00:21:34.877  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mom, don't send anything to the Captain.
Do you hear me?

407
00:21:35.044 --> 00:21:37.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Try boosting the deflector output.
-It's already at maximum.

408
00:21:37.671 --> 00:21:39.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>[staticky, garbled audio]</i>

409
00:21:39.924 --> 00:21:43.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Argh! I don't believe this!
I had a minute and a half left.

410
00:21:43.511 --> 00:21:44.929  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You'll have another opportunity
to speak with them

411
00:21:45.095 --> 00:21:47.097  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in approximately two months.

412
00:21:47.264 --> 00:21:49.266  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You just don't get it, do you?

413
00:21:49.433 --> 00:21:51.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

414
00:21:51.477 --> 00:21:53.479  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe if you had family
you were close to,

415
00:21:53.646 --> 00:21:55.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you'd feel a little differently.

416
00:21:59.860 --> 00:22:04.365  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Chief Medical Officer's</i>
<i>Personal Log, Stardate 54740.8.</i>

417
00:22:04.532 --> 00:22:07.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Although the decision has made me</i>
<i>unpopular with the crew,</i>

418
00:22:08.035 --> 00:22:09.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I've decided not</i>
<i>to compromise my work.</i>

419
00:22:09.995 --> 00:22:12.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'm making some final revisions</i>
<i>to the program</i>

420
00:22:12.331 --> 00:22:14.083  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>before transmitting it.</i>

421
00:22:15.501 --> 00:22:20.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Computer, run EMH program
<i>Photons Be Free.</i>

422
00:22:25.010 --> 00:22:28.346  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Welcome.
You've made an excellent choice.

423
00:22:28.514 --> 00:22:31.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're obviously a person
with impeccable taste.

424
00:22:31.392 --> 00:22:33.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Computer, freeze program.
-[computer] Unable to comply.

425
00:22:34.103 --> 00:22:38.399  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You are about to embark
on a remarkable journey.

426
00:22:38.566 --> 00:22:41.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You will take on the role
of a Medical Assistant

427
00:22:41.359 --> 00:22:43.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
aboard the Starship<i> Voyeur.</i>

428
00:22:43.445 --> 00:22:44.864  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Voyeur?</i>

429
00:22:45.030 --> 00:22:47.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your job will be to assist
the Chief Medical Officer

430
00:22:47.449 --> 00:22:50.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and learn to tolerate
his overbearing behavior

431
00:22:50.368 --> 00:22:53.122  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and obnoxious bedside manner.

432
00:22:54.957 --> 00:22:57.835  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Remember, patience is a virtue.

433
00:22:59.211 --> 00:23:00.462  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Paris]<i> Chapter One</i>

434
00:23:00.629 --> 00:23:03.549  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>"It's the Doctor's World,</i>
<i>You're Just Living In It."</i>

435
00:23:03.716 --> 00:23:07.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When I tell you
your shift begins at 0800,

436
00:23:07.678 --> 00:23:11.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that doesn't mean you can stroll in here
at 0800 and 24 seconds.

437
00:23:12.057 --> 00:23:13.267  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you understand me, Ensign?!

438
00:23:13.434 --> 00:23:15.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is outrageous!

439
00:23:15.436 --> 00:23:19.023  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What's outrageous is that I'm going
to miss my tee time.

440
00:23:19.189 --> 00:23:21.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, come along.

441
00:23:22.985 --> 00:23:25.029  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aw...

442
00:23:25.779 --> 00:23:28.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What seems to be the trouble,
One of Three?

443
00:23:28.365 --> 00:23:29.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm Two of Three.

444
00:23:29.700 --> 00:23:31.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[snide chuckle]
Sorry.

445
00:23:31.452 --> 00:23:33.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're triplets, you know?

446
00:23:33.537 --> 00:23:35.539  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It hurts when I do this.

447
00:23:35.706 --> 00:23:38.042  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, then, don't do it.
[laughing]

448
00:23:38.208 --> 00:23:40.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Ow!
-Ah, don't be a baby.

449
00:23:40.377 --> 00:23:41.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

450
00:23:41.795 --> 00:23:43.005  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[weary sigh]

451
00:23:43.172 --> 00:23:45.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Eh, your biradial clamp's
out of alignment.

452
00:23:45.841 --> 00:23:47.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I got just the thing.

453
00:23:48.010 --> 00:23:50.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[quietly]
It's a Klingon aphrodisiac--

454
00:23:50.679 --> 00:23:52.973  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
my own special blend.

455
00:23:56.560 --> 00:23:58.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You'll be feeling better...
-Mmm.

456
00:23:58.436 --> 00:24:00.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in no time at all.

457
00:24:00.356 --> 00:24:02.149  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sultry chuckle]

458
00:24:03.651 --> 00:24:05.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[both chuckling]

459
00:24:08.405 --> 00:24:10.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Lieutenant!
I want you to know

460
00:24:10.699 --> 00:24:12.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm making a full report to the Captain.

461
00:24:12.534 --> 00:24:15.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This isn't about that dermal regenerator
I misplaced, is it?

462
00:24:15.287 --> 00:24:16.872  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know very well
what this is about.

463
00:24:17.039 --> 00:24:18.791  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You accessed my holonovel
without permission

464
00:24:18.958 --> 00:24:21.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and replaced it with
your own hackneyed narrative.

465
00:24:21.377 --> 00:24:23.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hey, I'm just writing
what I know.

466
00:24:23.545 --> 00:24:26.048  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You destroyed a work of art
that took months to create.

467
00:24:26.215 --> 00:24:27.633  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Relax, Doc.

468
00:24:27.800 --> 00:24:30.302  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I saved your program
in a backup file,

469
00:24:30.468 --> 00:24:32.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I was just trying
to make a point.

470
00:24:32.888 --> 00:24:35.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, you made it with a typical
lack of subtlety.

471
00:24:35.391 --> 00:24:36.767  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, you're one to talk!

472
00:24:36.934 --> 00:24:40.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your program's about as subtle
as a Ferengi mating dance.

473
00:24:40.604 --> 00:24:42.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My program is a serious attempt
at social commentary.

474
00:24:42.898 --> 00:24:45.234  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yours is an insulting farce!
You...

475
00:24:45.401 --> 00:24:48.862  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[quietly] ...had me drugging a patient
and taking advantage of her.

476
00:24:49.029 --> 00:24:51.907  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't be ridiculous.
That character is not you.

477
00:24:52.074 --> 00:24:55.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
For one thing,
he has much more hair.

478
00:24:55.493 --> 00:24:58.038  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But what if some people
ran that program

479
00:24:58.205 --> 00:25:01.333  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and thought that it was based on you?
That would bother you, wouldn't it?

480
00:25:01.499 --> 00:25:04.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I don't care what people think.
-That's all you care about!

481
00:25:04.420 --> 00:25:07.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You want everyone back home to think
of you as a brilliant author.

482
00:25:08.007 --> 00:25:10.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not doing this for my ego,
and if you could look past yours,

483
00:25:10.926 --> 00:25:12.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
maybe you'd see that!

484
00:25:14.263 --> 00:25:16.098  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door opens, closes]

485
00:25:16.265 --> 00:25:21.020  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Listen... I don't care
if the whole Alpha Quadrant

486
00:25:21.186 --> 00:25:23.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
mistakes me
for Lieutenant Marseilles.

487
00:25:23.439 --> 00:25:26.984  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What bothers me is that you think
that's what I'm like.

488
00:25:27.151 --> 00:25:28.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Obviously, you're nothing like Marseilles.

489
00:25:28.736 --> 00:25:33.073  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-He's self-indulgent, immature.
-And how would you describe me?

490
00:25:34.366 --> 00:25:38.454  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, you're a married man
with a child on the way.

491
00:25:38.620 --> 00:25:39.913  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A lot of responsibilities.

492
00:25:40.080 --> 00:25:42.416  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm surprised you noticed.

493
00:25:44.001 --> 00:25:47.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, I thought
I'd begun to earn your respect.

494
00:25:47.254 --> 00:25:48.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe I was wrong.

495
00:25:51.133 --> 00:25:53.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your program is under file Theta-15.

496
00:25:53.802 --> 00:25:55.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do whatever you want with it.

497
00:26:05.105 --> 00:26:07.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Doctor, I need your help.

498
00:26:07.399 --> 00:26:10.694  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Unless you're suffering
acute symptoms, go away.

499
00:26:10.861 --> 00:26:14.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Um, I was wondering if you could
take a quick look at this.

500
00:26:15.741 --> 00:26:17.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Cooking with Neelix:</i>

501
00:26:17.493 --> 00:26:19.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>A Culinary Tour</i>
<i>of the Delta Quadrant.</i>

502
00:26:19.870 --> 00:26:21.121  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's a holo-cookbook proposal.

503
00:26:21.288 --> 00:26:23.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was hoping to transmit it
to your publisher

504
00:26:23.332 --> 00:26:25.125  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
during my com-link
this afternoon--

505
00:26:25.292 --> 00:26:27.252  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with your approval,
of course.

506
00:26:27.419 --> 00:26:28.712  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you're looking for writing tips,

507
00:26:28.879 --> 00:26:31.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
there are plenty of people on this ship
eager to offer them.

508
00:26:33.175 --> 00:26:35.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know what anyone else
may have told you,

509
00:26:35.552 --> 00:26:36.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but I loved your holonovel.

510
00:26:37.012 --> 00:26:38.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You did?
-Absolutely.

511
00:26:39.098 --> 00:26:40.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was a rousing adventure,

512
00:26:40.933 --> 00:26:42.768  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
with an important message, too.

513
00:26:42.935 --> 00:26:44.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Exactly.

514
00:26:44.436 --> 00:26:46.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is my first chance
to be appreciated,

515
00:26:46.480 --> 00:26:48.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
not just as a physician,
but as an artist.

516
00:26:48.606 --> 00:26:50.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought the crew
would be happy for me.

517
00:26:50.442 --> 00:26:51.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're going to reach
a wide audience.

518
00:26:52.152 --> 00:26:55.239  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What do you care about the opinions
of a few disgruntled shipmates?

519
00:26:55.405 --> 00:26:57.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're my friends.

520
00:26:57.783 --> 00:26:59.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't want to hurt them.

521
00:26:59.576 --> 00:27:03.413  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's an old Talaxian expression:

522
00:27:03.580 --> 00:27:06.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"When the road before you
splits in two,

523
00:27:06.917 --> 00:27:08.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
take the third path."

524
00:27:10.628 --> 00:27:12.464  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Meaning?

525
00:27:12.630 --> 00:27:15.134  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You could make some adjustments
to the program,

526
00:27:15.300 --> 00:27:18.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so it won't be so obvious
it's based on<i> Voyager.</i>

527
00:27:20.055 --> 00:27:22.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I suppose I could change the setting,

528
00:27:22.558 --> 00:27:24.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
alter the characters' physical parameters.

529
00:27:24.810 --> 00:27:27.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You wouldn't have
to change your theme.

530
00:27:27.521 --> 00:27:29.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

531
00:27:29.647 --> 00:27:31.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But a rewrite could take weeks.

532
00:27:31.608 --> 00:27:34.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My publisher is expecting
a final draft tomorrow.

533
00:27:34.862 --> 00:27:37.072  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe you should give him a call.

534
00:27:42.327 --> 00:27:43.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Revisions?</i>

535
00:27:43.829 --> 00:27:45.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I need to rework the characters.

536
00:27:45.539 --> 00:27:47.833  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Why?</i>
<i>They're so believable.</i>

537
00:27:48.000 --> 00:27:48.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[anxious laugh]

538
00:27:49.001 --> 00:27:51.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A little too believable,
apparently.

539
00:27:51.669 --> 00:27:54.089  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Doctor, I-I really don't think</i>
<i>this is necessary.</i>

540
00:27:54.256 --> 00:27:56.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm afraid I have to insist.

541
00:27:57.050 --> 00:27:59.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My friends' reputations
are at stake.

542
00:27:59.178 --> 00:28:00.888  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>[sighs]</i>

543
00:28:01.054 --> 00:28:03.849  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My publisher assures me
he won't distribute the program

544
00:28:04.016 --> 00:28:06.435  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
until he receives
the revised version.

545
00:28:06.602 --> 00:28:08.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That must be the one
where we assimilate the Borg

546
00:28:08.562 --> 00:28:10.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and take over the Quadrant.

547
00:28:12.232 --> 00:28:14.860  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're all grateful that you're taking
our feelings into account.

548
00:28:15.027 --> 00:28:17.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, how long do you expect
the revisions will take?

549
00:28:17.321 --> 00:28:19.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Art can't be rushed.

550
00:28:19.781 --> 00:28:22.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Take your time, Doctor.

551
00:28:25.703 --> 00:28:27.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Lieutenant.
-Hmm?

552
00:28:27.206 --> 00:28:28.332  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

553
00:28:28.498 --> 00:28:29.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh. Forget about it.

554
00:28:30.125 --> 00:28:32.044  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I could use your help
with the rewrites.

555
00:28:32.211 --> 00:28:33.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Really?

556
00:28:33.503 --> 00:28:37.007  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, you realize, as a writer,
I'm a little unsophisticated.

557
00:28:37.174 --> 00:28:40.594  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No, I believe the phrase
you're looking for is lowbrow.

558
00:28:45.224 --> 00:28:46.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey.

559
00:28:47.100 --> 00:28:48.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's that?

560
00:28:49.728 --> 00:28:52.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's from my father.

561
00:28:52.522 --> 00:28:54.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He wants to talk.

562
00:28:54.900 --> 00:28:57.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you gonna do?

563
00:28:57.402 --> 00:28:59.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I've already arranged
to talk with my cousin.

564
00:28:59.905 --> 00:29:03.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I'm sure she wouldn't mind
waiting a few weeks.

565
00:29:03.700 --> 00:29:05.827  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I wouldn't know
what to say to him.

566
00:29:05.994 --> 00:29:07.746  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then let him do the talking.

567
00:29:11.166 --> 00:29:12.459  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Look at you.</i>

568
00:29:12.626 --> 00:29:14.878  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You must be, what, 20 weeks along?</i>

569
00:29:15.045 --> 00:29:16.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
23, actually.

570
00:29:18.423 --> 00:29:19.633  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Have you decided on a name?</i>

571
00:29:19.800 --> 00:29:22.052  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not yet.

572
00:29:22.219 --> 00:29:24.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We were thinking about Miral.

573
00:29:26.098 --> 00:29:27.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Your mother would've liked that.</i>

574
00:29:28.809 --> 00:29:32.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You know, I had some business</i>
<i>on Kessik IV a few months ago.</i>

575
00:29:32.479 --> 00:29:35.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You wouldn't believe</i>
<i>what our old house looks like.</i>

576
00:29:35.482 --> 00:29:37.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lieutenant... 30 seconds.

577
00:29:39.611 --> 00:29:40.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We have less than a minute.

578
00:29:41.154 --> 00:29:43.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Is there a reason
you wanted to talk?

579
00:29:45.492 --> 00:29:48.662  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I know I can't make up for 20 years</i>
<i>in one conversation.</i>

580
00:29:50.080 --> 00:29:51.748  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The truth is...</i>

581
00:29:53.083 --> 00:29:55.335  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>when your ship disappeared,</i>

582
00:29:55.502 --> 00:29:57.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I thought I'd lost you.</i>

583
00:29:57.713 --> 00:29:59.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I don't expect you to forgive me,</i>

584
00:29:59.840 --> 00:30:03.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>but maybe we could try</i>
<i>to get to know each other again.</i>

585
00:30:03.927 --> 00:30:05.762  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[alarm chiming]

586
00:30:07.264 --> 00:30:08.557  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll write you.

587
00:30:19.943 --> 00:30:23.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[doors open, close]

588
00:30:31.079 --> 00:30:33.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry to disturb you, Admiral.

589
00:30:34.041 --> 00:30:35.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Uh, yes, Mr. Barclay.
What can I do for you?

590
00:30:35.959 --> 00:30:38.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought you'd want
to see this, sir.

591
00:30:38.378 --> 00:30:40.130  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, what is it?

592
00:30:40.297 --> 00:30:42.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's, um, a holonovel

593
00:30:42.507 --> 00:30:43.967  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that's becoming quite popular.

594
00:30:44.134 --> 00:30:45.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I appreciate
the gesture, Lieutenant,

595
00:30:46.053 --> 00:30:49.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I don't share your affinity
for holographic diversions.

596
00:30:49.681 --> 00:30:50.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You don't understand, sir.

597
00:30:50.807 --> 00:30:52.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This program...
it's about<i> Voyager,</i>

598
00:30:53.060 --> 00:30:56.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and it doesn't portray the crew
in a very flattering light.

599
00:30:58.648 --> 00:30:59.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm.

600
00:30:59.983 --> 00:31:01.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Janeway] On screen.

601
00:31:01.318 --> 00:31:02.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Admiral]<i> Captain.</i>

602
00:31:02.486 --> 00:31:04.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Seven told me
your message was urgent.

603
00:31:05.155 --> 00:31:08.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I had the dubious privilege</i>
<i>of playing a new holonovel,</i>

604
00:31:08.200 --> 00:31:10.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>apparently written by your EMH.</i>

605
00:31:10.452 --> 00:31:12.996  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'm surprised that you</i>
<i>would allow the Doctor</i>

606
00:31:13.163 --> 00:31:14.748  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>to discredit your crew like this.</i>

607
00:31:14.915 --> 00:31:16.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's still making revisions.

608
00:31:17.125 --> 00:31:19.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The program shouldn't
have been distributed yet.

609
00:31:19.836 --> 00:31:20.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Well, it has been.</i>

610
00:31:21.129 --> 00:31:22.923  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Mr. Barclay tells me</i>
<i>it's already being played</i>

611
00:31:23.090 --> 00:31:25.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>in thousands of holosuites.</i>

612
00:31:31.598 --> 00:31:34.101  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You assured me you
were going to wait for my revisions.

613
00:31:34.267 --> 00:31:38.021  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I demand that you recall every copy
and issue a public apology

614
00:31:38.188 --> 00:31:39.398  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to Captain Janeway and her crew.

615
00:31:39.564 --> 00:31:42.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I won't do anything of the sort.</i>

616
00:31:42.192 --> 00:31:44.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't see that you
have a choice, Mr. Broht.

617
00:31:44.694 --> 00:31:46.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Authors have rights.

618
00:31:46.446 --> 00:31:48.073  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Not in this case.</i>

619
00:31:48.240 --> 00:31:49.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you mean?

620
00:31:49.741 --> 00:31:52.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The Doctor is a hologram.</i>

621
00:31:52.452 --> 00:31:53.787  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So?

622
00:31:53.954 --> 00:31:59.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>According to Federation law,</i>
<i>holograms have no rights.</i>

623
00:32:07.217 --> 00:32:09.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Under a strict interpretation
of Federation law,

624
00:32:09.594 --> 00:32:13.223  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mr. Broht is correct.
The Doctor has no legal rights.

625
00:32:13.390 --> 00:32:14.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Because I'm a hologram.

626
00:32:14.891 --> 00:32:16.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

627
00:32:16.476 --> 00:32:18.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There is another option.

628
00:32:18.812 --> 00:32:20.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We may be able to claim
that the holonovel

629
00:32:20.564 --> 00:32:22.399  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
reveals classified information.

630
00:32:22.566 --> 00:32:26.111  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Starfleet could then request that
it be recalled for security purposes.

631
00:32:26.278 --> 00:32:28.238  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, great idea, a cover-up,

632
00:32:28.405 --> 00:32:30.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and then everyone will be convinced
that it's a true story.

633
00:32:30.782 --> 00:32:32.492  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Could we claim defamation?

634
00:32:32.659 --> 00:32:35.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, we'd have to prove
that the story's about us

635
00:32:35.579 --> 00:32:36.746  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and that we've been harmed by it.

636
00:32:36.913 --> 00:32:40.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We might win on those grounds,
but what about the Doctor?

637
00:32:40.876 --> 00:32:42.294  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about me, Captain?

638
00:32:42.461 --> 00:32:44.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's the crew's reputations
that are at risk.

639
00:32:45.005 --> 00:32:46.965  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not so sure.

640
00:32:47.132 --> 00:32:50.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I think it's your reputation
that's on the line here.

641
00:32:50.594 --> 00:32:54.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have the same rights as
every other member of this crew,

642
00:32:54.389 --> 00:32:56.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I'm not going to let
this publisher say otherwise.

643
00:33:01.271 --> 00:33:05.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Captain's Log,</i>
<i>Stardate 54748.6.</i>

644
00:33:05.192 --> 00:33:07.944  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>A Federation Arbitrator</i>
<i>has been assigned to determine</i>

645
00:33:08.111 --> 00:33:11.740  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>whether the Doctor has the right</i>
<i>to control his artistic creation.</i>

646
00:33:11.907 --> 00:33:13.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Because of our limited com time</i>
<i>with Earth,</i>

647
00:33:14.034 --> 00:33:16.953  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>the argument should take</i>
<i>about three days.</i>

648
00:33:17.120 --> 00:33:19.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You claim the Doctor</i>
<i>doesn't have the legal right</i>

649
00:33:19.456 --> 00:33:21.041  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>to control this holoprogram.</i>

650
00:33:21.208 --> 00:33:24.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Yet you're promoting the fact</i>
<i>that</i> Voyager's<i> EMH wrote it.</i>

651
00:33:24.377 --> 00:33:26.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Our most successful children's title

652
00:33:26.630 --> 00:33:29.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is a program "written by"
Toby the Targ.

653
00:33:30.133 --> 00:33:32.302  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Fortunately, Toby
hasn't tried to stop me

654
00:33:32.469 --> 00:33:35.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
from distributing any of his work.

655
00:33:35.305 --> 00:33:37.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But you don't deny that the Doctor
is the creator of this holonovel?

656
00:33:38.141 --> 00:33:43.063  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No, but, uh, a replicator
created this cup of coffee.

657
00:33:43.230 --> 00:33:45.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Should that replicator
be able to determine

658
00:33:45.649 --> 00:33:47.234  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
whether or not I can drink it?

659
00:33:47.400 --> 00:33:49.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I object!
-Doctor...

660
00:33:49.361 --> 00:33:51.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
An intriguing analogy, Mr. Broht,

661
00:33:51.863 --> 00:33:53.907  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I have never
encountered a replicator

662
00:33:54.074 --> 00:33:57.827  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that could compose music,
or paint landscapes,

663
00:33:57.994 --> 00:34:01.831  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or perform microsurgery.
Have you?

664
00:34:01.998 --> 00:34:03.542  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Would you say
that you have a reputation

665
00:34:03.708 --> 00:34:06.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
for publishing respected,
original works of literature?

666
00:34:07.003 --> 00:34:08.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd like to think so.

667
00:34:08.713 --> 00:34:11.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>And is the Doctor's holonovel</i>
<i>such a work?</i>

668
00:34:11.550 --> 00:34:14.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Actually, some aspects of it
are quite derivative.

669
00:34:15.053 --> 00:34:17.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tuvok] Has there even been
another work written

670
00:34:17.514 --> 00:34:19.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
about a hologram's struggle for equality?

671
00:34:19.599 --> 00:34:22.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Uh, not that I know of,
but, uh...

672
00:34:22.310 --> 00:34:24.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then, in that respect,
it is original?

673
00:34:26.189 --> 00:34:28.525  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I suppose so.

674
00:34:28.692 --> 00:34:32.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your Honor, Section Seven Gamma
of the Twelfth Guarantee

675
00:34:32.612 --> 00:34:36.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
defines an artist as a "person who creates
an original artistic work."

676
00:34:36.658 --> 00:34:39.953  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mr. Broht admits that the Doctor
created this program

677
00:34:40.120 --> 00:34:43.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and that it is original.
I therefore submit

678
00:34:43.248 --> 00:34:45.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that the Doctor should be entitled
to all rights and privileges

679
00:34:46.001 --> 00:34:48.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
accorded an artist
under the law.

680
00:34:51.298 --> 00:34:54.009  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>[sighs] You've made a persuasive</i>
<i>argument, Commander,</i>

681
00:34:54.175 --> 00:34:56.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>but there's a flaw in your logic.</i>

682
00:34:56.928 --> 00:34:59.014  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>As you point out, the law says</i>

683
00:34:59.180 --> 00:35:02.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>that the creator of an artistic work</i>
<i>must be a "person."</i>

684
00:35:02.767 --> 00:35:05.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Your EMH doesn't meet</i>
<i>that criteria.</i>

685
00:35:05.437 --> 00:35:06.688  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[static grows louder]

686
00:35:06.855 --> 00:35:09.524  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Barclay]<i> Sir, we're losing the link.</i>

687
00:35:09.691 --> 00:35:11.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>This hearing is in recess</i>
<i>until tomorrow.</i>

688
00:35:16.197 --> 00:35:18.116  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're not doing well.

689
00:35:18.283 --> 00:35:20.535  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Is that your considered
legal opinion?

690
00:35:21.786 --> 00:35:22.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

691
00:35:23.038 --> 00:35:25.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's just frustrating
to be told I have

692
00:35:25.332 --> 00:35:27.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
no more legal standing
than a replicator.

693
00:35:28.084 --> 00:35:31.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tuvok] If the Doctor doesn't have
the right to control his own work,

694
00:35:31.296 --> 00:35:33.173  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
then it stands to reason
he never had the right

695
00:35:33.340 --> 00:35:35.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to enter into an agreement
with Mr. Broht.

696
00:35:35.550 --> 00:35:38.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We could argue that
the original contract is invalid.

697
00:35:38.970 --> 00:35:41.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In other words,
you want to concede

698
00:35:41.348 --> 00:35:43.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that the Doctor isn't a person.

699
00:35:43.683 --> 00:35:45.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What we need to do...

700
00:35:46.227 --> 00:35:49.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is prove that he is just as much
a person as any of us.

701
00:35:50.023 --> 00:35:51.858  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How do we do that?

702
00:35:52.025 --> 00:35:54.027  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
By telling your real life story.

703
00:35:57.947 --> 00:36:00.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Because I was having difficulty</i>
<i>interacting with the crew,</i>

704
00:36:00.700 --> 00:36:02.410  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>the Doctor gave me social lessons.</i>

705
00:36:02.577 --> 00:36:05.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>First, he taught me</i>
<i>how to make conversation.</i>

706
00:36:05.372 --> 00:36:07.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Later, how to dance.

707
00:36:07.332 --> 00:36:09.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Eventually, he showed me

708
00:36:09.376 --> 00:36:12.003  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
how to express romantic interest.

709
00:36:12.170 --> 00:36:15.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Without his guidance, I wouldn't be</i>
<i>the person I am today.</i>

710
00:36:15.882 --> 00:36:18.927  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He decided it wasn't enough
to be just a doctor.

711
00:36:19.094 --> 00:36:21.888  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So he added command subroutines
to his matrix,

712
00:36:22.055 --> 00:36:23.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and now, in an emergency,

713
00:36:23.556 --> 00:36:25.767  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
he's as capable
as any Bridge officer.

714
00:36:25.934 --> 00:36:29.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That only proves the Doctor's program
can be modified.

715
00:36:29.437 --> 00:36:31.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Your Honor, I think it shows</i>
<i>he has a desire</i>

716
00:36:31.648 --> 00:36:35.026  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>to become more than he is,</i>
<i>just like any other person.</i>

717
00:36:35.193 --> 00:36:37.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He traveled halfway
across the galaxy

718
00:36:37.278 --> 00:36:40.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to care for Lewis Zimmerman,
the man who created his program.

719
00:36:41.157 --> 00:36:42.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was like a son

720
00:36:42.325 --> 00:36:45.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
who wanted to show his father
what he'd become,

721
00:36:45.578 --> 00:36:47.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so the old man
would be proud of him,

722
00:36:47.664 --> 00:36:51.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and if you ask me... he was.

723
00:36:51.334 --> 00:36:53.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I'd made myself clear,</i>

724
00:36:53.420 --> 00:36:56.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>but the Doctor disobeyed</i>
<i>my direct orders.</i>

725
00:36:56.715 --> 00:37:00.051  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>In the process,</i>
<i>he endangered the ship and crew.</i>

726
00:37:00.218 --> 00:37:02.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's hardly commendable behavior.

727
00:37:02.887 --> 00:37:06.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No, it wasn't,
but it was human.

728
00:37:06.683 --> 00:37:10.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Starfleet had programmed him</i>
<i>to follow orders.</i>

729
00:37:10.437 --> 00:37:12.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The fact that he was capable
of doing otherwise

730
00:37:13.106 --> 00:37:15.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
proves that he can think
for himself.

731
00:37:17.193 --> 00:37:18.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Janeway]<i> Your Honor,</i>

732
00:37:18.945 --> 00:37:21.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
centuries ago,
in most places on Earth,

733
00:37:21.990 --> 00:37:25.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
only landowners
of a particular gender and race

734
00:37:25.493 --> 00:37:27.287  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
had any rights at all.

735
00:37:27.454 --> 00:37:31.082  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Over time, those rights
were extended to all humans,

736
00:37:31.249 --> 00:37:33.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and later,
as we explored the galaxy,

737
00:37:33.960 --> 00:37:36.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to thousands
of other sentient species.

738
00:37:38.131 --> 00:37:40.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Our definition of what
constitutes a person

739
00:37:41.050 --> 00:37:43.052  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
has continued to evolve.

740
00:37:43.219 --> 00:37:47.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, we're asking that you expand
that definition once more...

741
00:37:47.557 --> 00:37:49.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to include our Doctor.

742
00:37:49.768 --> 00:37:52.979  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When I met him seven years ago,
I would never have believed

743
00:37:53.146 --> 00:37:56.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that an EMH could become
a valued member of my crew...

744
00:37:56.900 --> 00:37:59.277  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and my friend.

745
00:38:00.695 --> 00:38:02.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Doctor is a person

746
00:38:02.864 --> 00:38:06.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
as real as any flesh and blood
I have ever known.

747
00:38:06.785 --> 00:38:09.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>If you believe the testimony</i>
<i>you've heard here,</i>

748
00:38:09.746 --> 00:38:14.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it's only fair to conclude that he has
the same rights as any of us.

749
00:38:20.173 --> 00:38:21.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You'll have my decision
in two days.

750
00:38:23.051 --> 00:38:24.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>This hearing is in recess.</i>

751
00:38:36.898 --> 00:38:38.817  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When you sing<i> Happy Birthday</i>
to your mother,

752
00:38:38.983 --> 00:38:41.486  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-try to stay in tune.
-What's this?

753
00:38:41.653 --> 00:38:43.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
An isolinear chip
entitling the bearer

754
00:38:43.738 --> 00:38:45.782  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to three minutes
of com time tomorrow.

755
00:38:45.949 --> 00:38:48.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You made it clear how important it was
to finish your conversation.

756
00:38:49.160 --> 00:38:51.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I overreacted.

757
00:38:52.705 --> 00:38:55.041  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I understand why you did.

758
00:38:55.208 --> 00:38:57.293  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been observing the crew
interacting with their families

759
00:38:57.460 --> 00:38:59.128  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
over the past few days.

760
00:38:59.295 --> 00:39:02.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's become clear to me how meaningful
that communication can be.

761
00:39:06.845 --> 00:39:09.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks, but I can't accept this.

762
00:39:09.639 --> 00:39:11.015  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why not?

763
00:39:11.182 --> 00:39:13.142  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You should contact
your own family.

764
00:39:13.309 --> 00:39:15.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My parents were assimilated.

765
00:39:15.812 --> 00:39:17.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, there must be someone.

766
00:39:17.480 --> 00:39:19.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A distant relative?

767
00:39:20.316 --> 00:39:23.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My father has a sister
on Earth... Irene Hansen.

768
00:39:24.153 --> 00:39:27.907  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sure she'd be thrilled
to hear from you.

769
00:39:32.453 --> 00:39:34.163  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You can imagine my reaction</i>

770
00:39:34.330 --> 00:39:37.083  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>when Starfleet told me</i>
<i>to expect your call.</i>

771
00:39:37.250 --> 00:39:40.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I experienced some apprehension myself.

772
00:39:40.795 --> 00:39:43.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You seem like</i>
<i>a lovely young woman.</i>

773
00:39:44.591 --> 00:39:48.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>But you were the most stubborn</i>
<i>six-year-old I've ever met.</i>

774
00:39:49.053 --> 00:39:51.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Your parents left you with me</i>
<i>for a weekend,</i>

775
00:39:51.973 --> 00:39:55.101  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and you were so angry,</i>
<i>you locked yourself in my guest room</i>

776
00:39:55.268 --> 00:39:57.604  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and refused to come out.</i>

777
00:39:58.229 --> 00:40:01.065  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That must have been...
inconvenient for you.

778
00:40:01.232 --> 00:40:03.860  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Oh, I coaxed you out eventually...</i>

779
00:40:04.027 --> 00:40:06.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>with a strawberry tart.</i>

780
00:40:06.571 --> 00:40:08.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm very fond of strawberries.

781
00:40:08.531 --> 00:40:10.408  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I didn't realize
I'd eaten them as a child.

782
00:40:10.575 --> 00:40:13.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You couldn't get enough of them.</i>
<i>[laughs]</i>

783
00:40:13.202 --> 00:40:15.079  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Of course, you didn't hesitate</i>
<i>to point out</i>

784
00:40:15.246 --> 00:40:17.665  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>if they weren't perfectly ripe.</i>

785
00:40:19.250 --> 00:40:21.794  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry if I insulted you.

786
00:40:21.961 --> 00:40:23.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Perhaps I shouldn't have called.

787
00:40:24.130 --> 00:40:27.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>No, I'm very glad you did.</i>

788
00:40:27.508 --> 00:40:31.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It's wonderful</i>
<i>to see you again, Annika.</i>

789
00:40:38.227 --> 00:40:40.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're exploring new territory today,

790
00:40:40.355 --> 00:40:44.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so it is fitting that this hearing
is being held at Pathfinder.

791
00:40:44.525 --> 00:40:47.904  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Doctor exhibits many of the traits
we associate with a person--

792
00:40:48.071 --> 00:40:52.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
intelligence, creativity,
ambition, even fallibility.

793
00:40:52.825 --> 00:40:54.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But are these traits real,

794
00:40:54.827 --> 00:40:58.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or is the Doctor merely
programmed to simulate them?

795
00:40:59.082 --> 00:41:01.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
To be honest, I don't know.

796
00:41:02.001 --> 00:41:04.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Eventually,
we will have to decide,

797
00:41:04.504 --> 00:41:09.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
because the issue of holographic rights
isn't going to go away.

798
00:41:09.509 --> 00:41:11.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But at this time,
I am not prepared to rule

799
00:41:11.344 --> 00:41:14.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that the Doctor
is a person under the law.

800
00:41:14.180 --> 00:41:18.559  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
However, it is obvious he is
no ordinary hologram,

801
00:41:18.726 --> 00:41:21.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and while I can't say with certainty
that he is a person,

802
00:41:21.479 --> 00:41:24.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I am willing to extend
the legal definition of artist

803
00:41:24.482 --> 00:41:26.776  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to include the Doctor.
I therefore rule

804
00:41:26.943 --> 00:41:28.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that he has the right
to control his work,

805
00:41:28.861 --> 00:41:32.031  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I'm ordering all copies of his
holonovel to be recalled immediately.

806
00:41:32.198 --> 00:41:34.492  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Your Honor...
-This hearing is adjourned.

807
00:41:34.659 --> 00:41:37.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Congratulations, Doctor.
-Thank you, Reg.

808
00:41:37.286 --> 00:41:38.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>We'll be in touch, Captain.</i>

809
00:41:41.290 --> 00:41:42.542  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You don't look like someone

810
00:41:42.709 --> 00:41:45.712  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
who's just struck the first blow
for the rights of holograms.

811
00:41:45.878 --> 00:41:47.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't mean to sound ungrateful,

812
00:41:48.131 --> 00:41:51.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but it feels like a hollow victory--
pardon the pun.

813
00:41:51.592 --> 00:41:54.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The program's already been played
by thousands of people.

814
00:41:54.470 --> 00:41:56.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-The damage is done.
-We'll survive.

815
00:41:56.556 --> 00:42:00.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If I'm not mistaken, don't you have
a holonovel to revise?

816
00:42:00.518 --> 00:42:03.146  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do you think I'll be able
to find another publisher?

817
00:42:03.312 --> 00:42:05.857  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If there's one thing
I've learned about you, Doctor,

818
00:42:06.024 --> 00:42:08.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it's that you can do just about anything
you set your mind to.

819
